# Ware Design System & Build Pipeline

Every ware is a first-class app in the Bazaar ecosystem. These rules are non-negotiable for consistency, theming, and CI reliability.

---

## DESIGN SYSTEM — `@bazaar/design`

### Required imports in every `main.tsx`

```tsx
import { ErrorBoundary } from '@bazaar/design';
import '@bazaar/design/css';
```

- `@bazaar/design/css` activates the full token layer (`--bw-bg`, `--bw-surface`, `--bw-accent`, etc.)
- `<ErrorBoundary>` must wrap `<App>` — do **not** write a hand-rolled boundary class

### Set the colour scheme

When a ware has a fixed colour scheme, set it in `main.tsx` before rendering:

```tsx
// dark ware (most wares)
document.documentElement.setAttribute( 'data-theme', 'dark' );

// light ware
document.documentElement.setAttribute( 'data-theme', 'light' );
```

### Use design components for UI chrome

Do not re-implement these — import from `@bazaar/design`:

| Need | Component |
|---|---|
| Clickable action | `Button` |
| Text field | `Input` / `Textarea` / `Select` |
| Overlay | `Modal` |
| Status chip | `Badge` |
| Loading state | `Spinner` |
| Ephemeral notification | `ToastProvider` + `useToast` |

### CSS tokens — no hardcoded hex colours in theme-aware UI

```css
/* ❌ hardcoded — breaks dark/light switching */
.panel { background: #1e1e2e; color: #cdd6f4; }

/* ✅ token-driven */
.panel { background: var(--bw-bg); color: var(--bw-text); }
```

Canvas rendering colours (Matrix rain green, star white, etc.) are exempt — they are intentional and not theme-driven.

---

## BUILD PIPELINE

### `vite.config.ts` — canonical alias map (required)

Every ware's `vite.config.ts` must include this exact `resolve.alias` block so TypeScript and Vite both resolve monorepo packages from source:

```ts
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import react            from '@vitejs/plugin-react';
import { resolve }      from 'path';

export default defineConfig( {
  plugins: [ react() ],
  base: './',
  resolve: {
    alias: {
      '@bazaar/client':       resolve( __dirname, '../../packages/client/src/index.ts' ),
      '@bazaar/client/react': resolve( __dirname, '../../packages/client/src/hooks.ts' ),
      '@bazaar/design/theme': resolve( __dirname, '../../packages/design/src/theme/adminColor.ts' ),
      '@bazaar/design/css':   resolve( __dirname, '../../packages/design/src/css/index.css' ),
      '@bazaar/design':       resolve( __dirname, '../../packages/design/src/index.ts' ),
    },
  },
  build: {
    outDir:      'dist',
    emptyOutDir: true,
    assetsDir:   'assets',
    rollupOptions: {
      // React is provided by the shell's import map — declaring it external
      // prevents double-bundling and keeps React context consistent across wares.
      // Must match the "shared" array in manifest.json.
      external: [ 'react', 'react-dom', 'react/jsx-runtime' ],
    },
  },
  server: { cors: true },
} );
```

### `package.json` — required `package` script

Replace `{slug}` with the ware's slug:

```json
"scripts": {
  "dev":     "vite",
  "build":   "tsc -b && vite build",
  "preview": "vite preview",
  "package": "npm run build && cp manifest.json dist/ && cd dist && zip -r ../../{slug}.wp . && echo 'Packaged: {slug}.wp'"
}
```

### Register in `wares/registry.json`

Add an entry before the ware can be released:

```json
{
  "slug":         "{slug}",
  "name":         "{Name}",
  "description":  "One punchy sentence.",
  "version":      "1.0.0",
  "author":       "Regionally Famous",
  "icon_url":     "https://github.com/RegionallyFamous/bazaar/releases/latest/download/{slug}-icon.svg",
  "download_url": "https://github.com/RegionallyFamous/bazaar/releases/latest/download/{slug}.wp",
  "tags":         ["tag1", "tag2"]
}
```

### Register in CI — `.github/workflows/ci.yml`

Add a build step inside the `build-wares` job, after the last existing ware:

```yaml
- name: Build {slug}
  working-directory: wares/{slug}
  run: npm run package
```

---

## NEW WARE CHECKLIST

Before opening a PR or running `bin/build-zip.sh`:

- [ ] `@bazaar/design/css` imported in `main.tsx`
- [ ] `<ErrorBoundary>` from `@bazaar/design` wraps `<App>`
- [ ] `data-theme` attribute set in `main.tsx`
- [ ] `vite.config.ts` has the canonical alias map and `rollupOptions.external` matching the `shared` array in `manifest.json`
- [ ] `package.json` has the `package` script with the correct slug
- [ ] Entry added to `wares/registry.json`
- [ ] Build step added to `.github/workflows/ci.yml` `build-wares` job
- [ ] `npm run package` exits 0 from the ware directory
